coref_content: publish on Monday 7th September 2015 Minister for Natural Resources, Joe McHugh, today welcome new job creation statistic show that Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company report the addition of 134 new job in the first six month of 2015. Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) be an integrate network of 25 company, bring expertise in water, mineral and infrastructure development to global client in over 50 country. launch in September 2012 as a government measure to help business win work in international market, Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) be support by the Geological Survey of Ireland and Enterprise Ireland. the positive job creation record by Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company be an important contributor to Ireland's export economy and demonstrate ability and capacity by irish professional geoscience service to win business in highly competitive market. recent project win include design and construction of 15 water supply scheme in Ethiopia fund by the European Investment Bank ; investigation for a 45 km water supply pipeline in Malawi fund by the World Bank ; Environmental Impact Statements for a marine terminal in California ; lining material for a ghanaian gold mine ; Waste Water Treatment plant in Turkey and revetment design for marine work in Bahrain. the addition of 134 new job in the first six month of 2015 be the large number of job create by Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company in a six month period and contrast with a reduction in job number of 32 report at 31st December 2014. the recovery in net job creation as at 30th June 2015 be account for by 1 ) continued growth in service provide for infrastructure development and extractive industry in the UK, the Gulf Region and Western Africa, and 2 ) partial reversal of layoff in late 2014 experience by service provider to the irish mining sector. Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company provide design, consultancy and contracting service to multilateral agency, government and the private sector. Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company employ almost 1,200 person and have a collective turnover of € 252 million in 2014, of which 64 % come from overseas business. comment on today welcome new job creation statistic, Minister for Natural Resources, Joe McHugh, say the necessary reduction in infrastructure spend in Ireland since 2009 highlight the importance of develop overseas market for irish professional geoscience service. about half of the 257 new job create by Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company since late 2014 be in international market. the continue success of Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company in create well pay sustainable job validate the support model provide by the Geological Survey of Ireland and Enterprise Ireland for these business. GSI plan to continue support for the Geoscience Ireland project into 2017. " future event in which Geoscience Ireland ( GI ) member company will participate be the Trade Mission to Western Africa in November 2015 and the PDAC Convention in Canada in March 2016. note to editor for further information on Geoscience Ireland ( GI ), please see
